    {
      "type": "prompt",
      "id": "LYUeR",
      "x": -30,
      "y": -500,
      "width": 836,
      "height": 229,
      "content": "i want to make a web application design to use lerobot framework on so101 and bimanual so 101 arms setups easier. There should be multiple pages. The features include connect the ports of the arms, calibrate the arms, teleoperate the arms, look at all the cameras connected, and record data. \n\nThe ports of the every arm should be discovered already, so the first page i imagine would be to let users label each arm, users should label which are leader and which are follower, and for bimanual setup there should be a way to label left and right. The first page should also show the camera feed for every available camera and let the user pick which would be included when recording data\n\nThe next page would be calibration page, the arms need to be calibrated, there could be multiple calibration for each arm with a unique calibration file name. users could create a new calibration when needed. Calibration is split into two steps, first the robot moves to the central position and then the user can click enter and then the user proceeds to move all the joints to its min and max position and then when done click enter to finish. Make these 2 pages first"
    },
